title: 'Stranger Things' Kids Walk the 2017 Golden Globes Red Carpet, and We Can't Handle the Cuteness!
text: 'Stranger Things' Kids Walk the 2017 Golden Globes Red Carpet, and We Can't Handle the Cuteness! by Desiree Murphy 4:25 PM   Photo: Getty Images Nothing strange here! The young stars of Netflix's Stranger Things attended the 74th Annual Golden Globes at the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Los Angeles on Sunday, looking cuter than ever while posing for photographs on the red carpet. WATCH: 'Stranger Things': 7 Things We Learned From the Season 2 Table Read Millie Bobby Brown pulled out all the stops with her Globes ensemble, stepping out in a flashy silver number by Jenny Packham, which she paired with metallic heels. She kept her beauty look simple, sporting a punchy pink pout, silver eyeshadow and slicked-back hair. Photo: Getty Images Her co-stars, Caleb McLaughlin, Finn Wolfhard, Noah Schnapp and Gaten Matarazzo, also dressed to impress, all rocking black-and-white variations of the classic tux. Photo: Getty Images It's sure to be a memorable night for this tight-knit crew, as Stranger Things is nominated for Best TV Series, Drama against The Crown , Westworld , Game of Thrones and This Is Us . See how they reacted to the exciting nomination in the video below!
